On March 16, Yiliang County, Zhaotong, Yunnan Province, reported the investigation and handling of the case of "medical workers voluntarily giving up their claim for epidemic relief" . According to the circular, the investigation did not reveal any cases in which the hospital requested and unified medical staff to waive their claim for benefits, but there were cases in which information on the relevant benefits policies was not available and, to this end, the Yiliang County Party Committee and the county government have instructed the county people's Hospital to immediately rectify the problems in the previous stage of work, earnestly strengthen the organization and leadership of the statistical reporting work and the training of policy promotion, and ensure that the accurate statistical reporting can fulfill the subsidies, the state to the front-line medical care and care policy to meet the conditions of each medical staff. In the next step of work, the implementation of the policy is not in place, organizations and individuals will be seriously held accountable.

The full text of the communication is as follows:

Recently, the media published a report that some medical staff of Yiliang County People's Hospital in Zhaotong City, Yunnan Province had voluntarily given up their claims for temporary work subsidies to fight the epidemic, which triggered heated discussion on the Internet and caused adverse effects. In this regard, the Yiliang County Party Committee, the county government expressed deep apologies, and instructed the relevant departments to form an investigation team to enter the county people's Hospital to carry out an investigation and verify. The preliminary investigation is being reported to the community as follows:

The Yiliang County, Zhaotong People's Hospital has 608 staff. In accordance with the relevant provisions of the circular of the Yunnan Provincial Health and Health Commission on the compilation of statistics on subsidies for temporary work of personnel engaged in the prevention and control of the epidemic of new coronavirus (hereinafter referred to as the circular) , the Yiliang County, Zhaotong People's Hospital on March 1 completed the implementation of various types of subsidies for the implementation of the staff statistics and internal publicity work units, to report subsidies for a total of 126 personnel. The investigation did not find out the situation that the hospital asked and Unified Organization medical staff to abandon the claim for subsidy.

The Yiliang County, Zhaotong People's Hospital did not uniformly organize the medical personnel to carry out accurate and comprehensive publicity and explanation on the relevant procedures and approval requirements stipulated in the circular in the statistical reporting of temporary work subsidies to its frontline staff, led to some medical staff in the relevant provisions of the understanding is not in place, in the report has not been completed and approved and obtain subsidies in the case of the expression of the will to give up the claim for subsidies, the hospital did not stop.

To this end, the Yiliang County Party Committee and the county government have instructed the county people's Hospital to immediately rectify the problems existing in the previous stage of work, and earnestly strengthen the organization and leadership of the statistical reporting work, as well as the work of policy publicity and training, to ensure strict compliance with the requirements of the circular of the State Council on the Joint Mechanism for the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia (no. 10[2020] of the State Council) on focusing on first-line implementation of measures to protect and care medical personnel, the accurate statistics report cashes the subsidy, earnestly carries out the state to the front-line medical personnel's care policy to meet the condition each medical personnel. In the next step of work, the implementation of the policy is not in place, organizations and individuals will be seriously held accountable. I sincerely thank all sectors of society for my concern, care and understanding of the county work, and urge all sectors of society to continue to care, support, and supervise the county to implement the state's care and care of the first-line medical staff follow-up related work.
